title: Bold yet Classic Logo for New Forestry and Land Clearing Business
description:
Forestry mulching is a land clearing method which uses specific types of machinery to cut and grind trees and other vegetation. The ground mulch is left behind on the earth , which is used for beautification, and also to nourish the forest floor. Forest mulching is great for forest fire mitigation / prevention, to build roads, to clear for building, for beautification, and for any other land clearing purpose. Clientele can include: State and federal parks, real estate agents, home owners, large parcel owners such as timber companies, etc.
Please read the "Is there anything else you would like to communicate to the designers?" and attached imagery document to understand our logo needs. We are getting a lot of minimalist designs - the problem with this is that not a lot of people know what forestry mulching is, so they need a visual representation. Thank you very much for your hard work!
other_notes:
Overall Logo Concept:
Our concept is our name generally centered on the logo. Then, flanking each side of the business name, is a piece of equipment mulching a tree, with the pine tree falling away from the company name. Both pieces of equipment would generally look like equipment we actually use. I included a rough picture of what I am describing.
One side (the left side) would be the larger piece of equipment (Fecon Equipment) and the right side would be the smaller (ASV Equipment). I included pictures of these pieces of equipment.
The smaller equipment would have its arm somewhat raised to appear more aggressive. I included pictures of machines with the raised arm on the smaller-type.
I like logos that look sophisticated, not cartoony.
It is important to me that the logo look good whether it is on the side of a truck, or printed small on a business card or letterhead. This may or may not include simplifying small details on machinery.
I think that I prefer a rectangular shape (running horizontally) because this shape would take up more space on a business card or truck as opposed to a circle.
We are open to a concept which is ENTIRELY different from our idea above, as you are an experienced artist and probably have wonderful ideas.

title: Trustworthy, earnest, and serious dog logo for a real estate company
description:
We empower clients to live the lifestyle they desire by helping create their own Airbnb business. We offer expertise in selection (real estate market and property to invest in), structure (business and legal structuring), and execution (we are a team of real estate professionals that help with every step in the process of purchasing real estate and creating an Airbnb).
Essentially, we help people buy properties and turn them into cash-flowing Airbnbs and create the structure that allows them to stay at their Airbnb for personal use. We are a real estate services firm.
The target audience is 25-35 year-olds and 55-70 year-olds with $75K - $150K in investable assets that want to diversify into real estate but don't know how and want access to their own beach house.
other_notes: We want the logo to give off the following emotions: trustworthiness, friendly, earnestness, focus, and happiness. Our current logo's eyes look too sad and the smile does not look earnest. We are open to different types of dogs, but we want a dog to be our mascot. We like the font we currently have but are open to suggestions. We also would like some (but not too much) color incorporated into the logo. A silhouette of a dog or an actual dog (similar to our existing logo) would be interesting.

title: Books and media recommendations app
description:
rankxt is a recommendation and tracking mobile app. The first version is for books. Then we will follow with versions for thing like movies, TV, music, podcasts. The app will be simple and intuitive. It will be visually fun, showing book covers and having books compete against each other to determine rankings.
We're looking for a design that conveys the * action * of people texting recommendations of the titles they rank the highest.
The name rankxt combines texting with ranking, and the flow is:
1. Search for a book you've read and add it to the list of books you have read.
2. Text the book to a friend you think will like it.
3. Your friend can accept the recommendation and it gets added to their list of books "To Read."
4. Titles will be ranked by comparing 2 items together and having the user choose which item is better. So the most compelling items rise to the top for each user.
The logo should be generic enough to cover books now, and movies, music, TV, podcasts etc in the future. But maybe have a consistent theme, where the books, tv, etc symbol rotates out depending on which one is being used. We are open to ideas here.
Audience is adults who consume media, starting with books.
other_notes: The logo will be the App Icon.
